  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `any`\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\nCommit hash : `any`\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nWrite a log file with usefull logs on INFO or DEBUG level by default.\n\nAs a moderator on Stack Exchange, I'm at the frontline of user support and I keep getting questions like [why is my connected peers so few and blocks syncronising so slow even it stops](http://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/3355/87).\n\nMy first reaction is to ask about which version they are running and which backend. Sometimes they don't even know it's geth. And also not which version.\n\nThe second reaction would be to ask what appears in the logs. But since most users simply double click the mist wallet dapp, the logs are lost in stdout somewhere.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nUser has to manually pipe the log to a file (and to know how to use a command line).\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nRun `geth`.\n#### Rationale\n\nI fear this might be closed as \"works as desired\", I see [piping is the way to go](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Getting-Geth#using-stderr). But at least I would like to get an opinion, why there is no debug logging enabled and maybe an indication if this could be implemented or not.\n",
