    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Thank you for helping with user support!\n\nMist writes logs to a file by default. The log files are rotated and stored in a platform-specific directory.\nOn OS X, the latest log is `~/Library/Application Support/Mist/node.log`\nOn Windows, it is `C:\\Users\\<name>\\AppData\\Roaming\\Mist\\node.log`.\nThere used to be a button in the Mist menu that opens this folder.\n\ngeth itself is intended to run in many environments and logging to a file isn't always feasible or the best way. While we won't add log file support to geth in the near future, I hope that the Mist logs will make your life easier.\n",
