    "body": "I agree that geth approach to logs is \"very interesting\". I find it's very strange that geth doesn't send logs to expected location by default (e.g. /var/log/geth.log for Linux/UNIX, not sure what's on Windows). \n\nIn what kind of environment environment not having logs are desire? Are they majority of us cases? If they are 'edge' cases I suggest to flip logic. Enable logs by default, but add option to stop them when needed.\n",
